    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework demonstrates adequate credibility for the COU. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; 12 of 13 meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the COU is restricted to standard ASTM F1717 quasi-static conditions where rate sensitivity is negligible for titanium constructs. All six quantitative validation comparisons satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The package is accepted for regulatory submission.",
